Chicago and Boston Marathon winner Rita Jeptoo failed a September doping test, her agent revealed Friday.

Federico Rosa said that the 33-year-old  Kenyan tested positive for a banned substance in a test in Kenya before she won the Chicago Marathon in October.

Rosa said Jeptoo's 'A' sample tested positive and that they were now waiting for testing on a 'B' sample.

