Rosa said he learned of the failed test 'a few days ago' and did not name the substance that showed up in the test. 

'We will legally go after the person or the people that convinced Rita to do this,' Rosa said, saying that her management had 'nothing to do with' the doping. 

'I am sorry for Rita,' Rosa said.

Jeptoo won back-to-back titles in both the Chicago and Boston Marathons, setting a course record in April in Boston. Doping tests at the time came back negative. 

She also currently leads the World Marathon Majors, a championship-style competition across multiple cities.

The series announced the postponement of the awards ceremony, scheduled for Sunday, because of the positive test.

